  "prompt": "Do boys get friendzoned?",
  "response": "Yes, boys can experience being \"friendzoned,\" which is when someone they are interested in romantically only sees them as a friend and does not reciprocate their romantic feelings. This situation can happen to anyone, regardless of gender. While the concept of being \"friendzoned\" is often discussed in popular culture, it's important to approach relationships with respect and understanding and to recognize that mutual consent and feelings are crucial in any romantic connection.",
